+# The upstream WORKSPACE configures a devcontainer-specific Bazel crosstool
+# (expecting /usr/bin/<arch>-linux-gnu-gcc) and pre-built AWS/Azure/GCP SDKs
+# under /opt. Those are only used by the s3/gcs/azure backends, which ship as
+# separate Python wheels (runai_model_streamer_{s3,gcs,azure}) that dlopen their
+# own .so files at runtime. The core libstreamer.so bundled by this wheel has no
+# third-party C++ dependencies, so we drop all of the above and let Bazel
+# auto-detect the conda-forge compiler (CC/CXX) instead.
